SIMPLE: flaw
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flaw
<hw>Flaw</hw> <pr>(fl⟦add⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>flai</ets>, <ets>flaw</ets> flake; cf. Sw. <ets>flaga</ets> flaw,
crack, breach, flake, D. <ets>vlaag</ets> gust of wind, Norw.
<ets>flage</ets>, <ets>flaag</ets>, and E. <ets>flag</ets> a flat
stone.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A crack or breach; a gap or fissure; a
defect of continuity or cohesion; <as>as, a <ex>flaw</ex> in a knife or
a vase</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This heart⟦br⟧
Shall break into a hundered thousand <qex>flaws</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A defect; a fault; <as>as, a <ex>flaw</ex> in
reputation; a <ex>flaw</ex> in a will, in a deed, or in a
statute.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Has not this also its <qex>flaws</qex> and its dark side?</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A sudden burst of noise and disorder; a tumult;
uproar; a quarrel.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And deluges of armies from the town⟦br⟧
Came pouring in; I heard the mighty <qex>flaw</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A sudden burst or gust of wind of short
duration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Snow, and hail, and stormy gust and <qex>flaw</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like <qex>flaws</qex> in summer laying lusty corn.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Blemish; fault; imperfection; spot;
speck.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flaw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Flaw
<hw>Flaw</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Flawed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Flawing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To crack; to make
flaws in.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The brazen caldrons with the frosts are <qex>flawed</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To break; to violate; to make of no effect.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>France hath <qex>flawed</qex> the league.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>flawed</ent>⟦br⟧
